                            <comment id="13529592" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 12 Dec 2012 03:08:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See also &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-829&quot; title=&quot;Add /zookeeper/sessions/* to allow inspection/manipulation of client sessions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;ZOOKEEPER-829&quot;&gt;ZOOKEEPER-829&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13529844" author="nkeywal" created="Wed, 12 Dec 2012 11:13:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is there a security impact if we keep the password in a file? We can do some dissimulation, but it&apos;s will have to be readable, at least by the user account used to start/stop hbase.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13530193" author="enis" created="Wed, 12 Dec 2012 18:39:53 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Is there a security impact if we keep the password in a file? We can do some dissimulation, but it&apos;s will have to be readable, at least by the user account used to start/stop hbase.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good question. If we make that file only readable by the hbase user it should be fine I think, since he has access to the credentials anyway. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
